The second annual CrossFit Kwetu charity ball rode on the success of last year's events. This year, the organisers upped the ante, electing to bridge the gap for five young men who are part of a mentorship programme led by coach Winnie Okoth.The event sought to raise enough funds for a year of their tuition and costs of transport and meals, as they continue the mentorship programme at the gym.The event took place at the Villa Rosa Kempinski.